<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution in south-eastern and southern-central France, ranging from Alpes-de-Haute-Provence and Hautes-Alpes to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Isère">Isere</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Drôme">Drome</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ardèche">Ardeche</normalizedToken>
, Vaucluse, Aveyron, Lot and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lozère">Lozere</normalizedToken>
. Based on phenotype (and geography - 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be recognised as valid because its location is within the distributional range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), we see no justification for 
<bibRefCitation author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B20" refString="Leraut, P, 2012. Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids. NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Leraut’s">Leraut's</normalizedToken>
(2012
</bibRefCitation>
: 98) reinstatement of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid subspecies under which he placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tremewan" authorityYear="1961" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aragonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aragonia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus aragonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mazel" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms (see also below). Even in the original description, Dujardin compared 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dujardin" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, stating that the forewing ground colour was similar. Consequently, it is here reinstated as a synonym (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">syn. rev.</emphasis>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Oberthuer" authorityYear="1909" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as placed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" refId="B17" refString="Hofmann, A, Tremewan, WG, 1996. A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae). Harley Books, Colchester" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 131).
</paragraph>
